tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul.
  The generic design was replaced with a calming, sleep-themed visual language,
  including a new color palette, improved layouts, and polished UI components
  across all sections and the final report.
overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetics of their sleep questionnaire
  app from a generic look to a more beautiful and professional design. I began
  by thoroughly reviewing the existing visual elements, identifying areas like
  the color palette, backgrounds, form sections, and UI components as needing
  significant improvement. The core approach involved introducing a calming,
  sleep-themed color palette (indigos, purples, teals) and applying it
  consistently. I redesigned the main questionnaire form, enhanced the welcome
  (IntroSection) with feature cards and a hero element, and polished individual
  UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and the progress bar.
  Crucially, I ensured consistent styling across all questionnaire sections by
  replacing old gray-boxed layouts with new, refined card-style groupings. The
  final report section also received a visual upgrade to align with the new
  theme. The outcome is an app with a cohesive, calming, and professional
  aesthetic that is well-suited for a sleep health assessment.
